description:
In 1849, Ellen White's husband, James White travelled to Middletown, Connecticut with copies of the Present Truth. It was here that he took the steps to become a global publishing ministry. This was the start of literature evangelism, which has been key to spreading the gospel all over the world. Many years later, James met a young man named George White, who was desperate to become a preacher. After many years to failure, he eventually became a fireside preacher, and it was here that he persuaded publishers to create special books to be used in the homes that he was visiting. 

To find out more information about George King & literature evangelism read our extended article on our website. 
https://lineagejourney.com/read/literature-evangelism-and-george-king
